1
00:00:01,240 --> 00:00:02,560
Hi everyone.

2
00:00:03,260 --> 00:00:05,540
Now I'll show several interesting experiments.

3
00:00:05,720 --> 00:00:08,840
So, the receiving and transmitting coils are ready.

4
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:11,600
This is the receiving Tesla coil.

5
00:00:11,700 --> 00:00:17,800
The load will be a 15 W lamp, diode bridge, capacitor.

6
00:00:17,980 --> 00:00:21,220
Measurement we'll do by DC — this is our voltmeter.

7
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:26,880
So, first test launch in continuous generation mode.

8
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:31,680
Generation, as usual, all starts without any interruptions.

9
00:00:33,380 --> 00:00:38,500
In this mode we have the consumption of the control logic part.

10
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:48,020
This lab block will record the power consumption of the common system.

11
00:00:49,880 --> 00:01:00,920
I now raise the current, voltage I regulated, the system doesn't even start because of very strong influence from receiving coil onto transmitting.

12
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:04,200
Need to step them apart a little.

13
00:01:04,680 --> 00:01:06,400
Now I approach.

14
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:13,880
See, the current grew for us, and what do we observe.

15
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:21,900
As usual, the fluorescent lamp glows, the lamp doesn't glow for us.

16
00:01:23,420 --> 00:01:34,200
Near the transmitting Tesla the fluorescent lamp glows very poorly, and near the receiving it glows well.

17
00:01:34,420 --> 00:01:35,440
This is already interesting.

18
00:01:35,980 --> 00:01:40,740
Now look what we have on transmitting first.

19
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:46,620
There's actually nothing here.

20
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:50,280
Only touching on the receiving.

21
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:54,120
On receiving it's livelier.

22
00:01:54,540 --> 00:02:03,480
See the discharge, you can see that non-chlorobe melts from the discharge, drops flow.

23
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:07,320
Such a hot Tesla came out.

24
00:02:08,940 --> 00:02:15,680
Well, and that's it, we won't get more besides the interesting moment you could see here.

25
00:02:16,180 --> 00:02:24,240
For some reason on the receiving Tesla we have much more field and much higher voltage.

26
00:02:24,340 --> 00:02:25,280
Experiment number 2.

27
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:32,500
I disconnected the lamp and disconnected grounding the inductor from its middle point.

28
00:02:33,140 --> 00:02:36,880
Now we'll do modulation with frequency 50 Hz.

29
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:41,280
The modulating pulse duration for us is 1%.

30
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:46,520
I switched the system to modulation mode, this is consumption of the logic control part.

31
00:02:47,260 --> 00:02:50,100
Now I raise the supply voltage.

32
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:59,680
This consumption we record now.

33
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:03,220
Electrolytic at input, 470 µF.

34
00:03:05,140 --> 00:03:10,880
I apply 200 V to the system.

35
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:14,320
You hear the characteristic 50 Hz sound.

36
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:23,760
It even echoes from above in the rafters.

37
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:28,580
Look at the voltage on the transmitting part.

38
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:31,080
Breakdown distance.

39
00:03:36,980 --> 00:03:41,600
Breakdown starts about 5 cm.

40
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,740
Receiving part.

41
00:03:50,060 --> 00:03:53,600
Breakdown at distance of 10-12 cm.

42
00:04:01,910 --> 00:04:05,210
Now we'll do the same manipulation.

43
00:04:05,330 --> 00:04:07,570
Pay attention to consumption.

44
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:19,640
We clearly have a voltage excess on the receiving coil.

45
00:04:21,420 --> 00:04:23,120
Once more transmitting.

46
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:28,100
Here at least 2 times lower.

47
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:39,500
And this is already an interesting phenomenon — we created a vortex with interruption help, and energy already went to the receiving Tesla transformer.

48
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:42,420
So, experiment number 3.

49
00:04:43,060 --> 00:04:47,800
I connected the lamp, connected grounding to the inductor middle point.

50
00:04:49,180 --> 00:04:51,820
What will we record at this experiment input?

51
00:04:52,600 --> 00:05:03,580
We'll record that we have a load, the lamp will glow, and we'll have voltage excess on the Tesla transformer itself.

52
00:05:04,100 --> 00:05:07,920
The inductor is now wound, as they say, randomly — first available.

53
00:05:08,020 --> 00:05:11,160
By length I didn't pick it, that'll need to be done later.

54
00:05:11,540 --> 00:05:18,060
Just to show the essence that the system can simultaneously give and still have a reserve.

55
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:26,780
Also for us the interruption will go at frequency 50 Hz, at duration 1%.

56
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:37,040
Here 50 Hz, I raise voltage on the transmitting Tesla, also 200 V.

57
00:05:51,410 --> 00:05:54,390
So, you see the lamp lit.

58
00:05:57,170 --> 00:06:04,270
Voltage on the lamp is 150 V, 155, slightly higher.

59
00:06:04,870 --> 00:06:14,370
I checked, and if voltage on this lamp is 150 V, it burns exactly at half-glow — a 15 V lamp at 7.5 V.

60
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:16,310
Consumption.

61
00:06:17,650 --> 00:06:18,750
Common system.

62
00:06:19,530 --> 00:06:22,270
See the voltage on the transmitting part.

63
00:06:26,810 --> 00:06:31,350
Breakdown about 5 cm on the receiving.

64
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:37,900
Breakdown now about 8 cm.

65
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:42,560
An interesting phenomenon turns out.

66
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:59,940
We load the receiving Tesla transformer with some load, take power off, and it has a voltage amplitude excess on the secondary coil relative to the primary.

67
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:02,160
And now we have the consumption.

68
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:07,120
How much is it there — twice 8, 16.

69
00:07:09,020 --> 00:07:20,100
It turns out for us that the system consumes 16 V, 7.5 V output, and excess on the secondary coil.

70
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,400
That is, what's the conclusion.

71
00:07:22,140 --> 00:07:26,940
That in the system we must use modulations.

72
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:31,120
This is the most usual modulation, now without any phase shifts.

73
00:07:32,340 --> 00:07:41,460
The check of this experiment is that with the coordination of two systems they're now tuned.

74
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:50,440
The transmitting and receiving coils are identical, tuned to one and the same frequency — that is, parameters maintained.

75
00:07:51,420 --> 00:07:54,060
And we have such an interesting effect.

76
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:58,100
This is the answer to the question people ask.

77
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:04,300
Can there be more energy on the receiving Tesla transformer than on the transmitting?

78
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:07,480
In modulation mode, naturally, yes.

79
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:18,740
If the Tesla transformer starts just in mode without modulation, you won't see such effects, or they'll be weak as I showed in experiment number one.

80
00:08:20,420 --> 00:08:23,620
Make conclusions yourselves, and we work further.
